{"id":"sword","term":"Sword","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Of the Hebrew was pointed, sometimes two-edged, was worn in a sheath, and suspended from the girdle (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 32:27\">Ex. 32:27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 31:4\">1 Sam. 31:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 21:27\">1 Chr. 21:27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 149:6\">Ps. 149:6</a>: <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 5:4\">Prov. 5:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 16:40\">Ezek. 16:40</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 21:3\">21:3-5</a>).</p>\n<p>It is a symbol of divine chastisement (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 32:25\">Deut. 32:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 7:12\">Ps. 7:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 78:62\">78:62</a>), and of a slanderous tongue (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 57:4\">Ps. 57:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 64:3\">64:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 12:18\">Prov. 12:18</a>). The word of God is likened also to a sword (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 4:12\">Heb. 4:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ephesians 6:17\">Eph. 6:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 1:16\">Rev. 1:16</a>). Gideon’s watchword was, “The sword of the Lord” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Judges 7:20\">Judg. 7:20</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 32:27","1 Samuel 31:4","1 Chronicles 21:27","Psalms 149:6","Proverbs 5:4","Ezekiel 16:40","Ezekiel 21:3","Deuteronomy 32:25","Psalms 7:12","Psalms 78:62","Psalms 57:4","Psalms 64:3","Proverbs 12:18","Hebrews 4:12","Ephesians 6:17","Revelation 1:16","Judges 7:20"]}